    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-08-24T17:02:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-08-24T17:02:00-05:00" n="105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <head>105. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Turkey</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d105fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 785.56/8–2457. Secret; Priority. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RSW1">Rockwell</persName>; cleared with <gloss
                            target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss>; and approved and signed by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>. Also sent to Amman and repeated to
                        Istanbul and to Paris for <gloss target="#t_USCINCEUR1">USCINCEUR</gloss>
                        and DEFREPNAMA.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-08-24T18:02:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 24, 1957—6:02 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>569. We have been holding conversations with King <persName corresp="#p_Hussein1"
                        >Hussein</persName> concerning the types of military items which we might
                    assist Jordan to obtain through the $10 million we have made available for this
                    purpose. On August 19 in Amman King in conversation with <persName
                        corresp="#p_MLD1">Mallory</persName> asked that we consider furnishing
                    regiment (which would be 36) of [<hi rend="italic">with</hi>] M47 tanks.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d105fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MLD1">Mallory</persName> reported the conversation in
                        telegram 336 from Amman, August 21. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi>
                        785.56/8–2157)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Ankara should inform King we agree furnish this number M47s.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d105fn3">King <persName corresp="#p_Hussein1">Hussein</persName> was
                        in Turkey August 22–25.</note> We assume he will wish also obtain at least
                    one year’s spare parts for each tank as well as ammunition.</p>
                <pb facs="0191" n="159" xml:id="pg_159"/>
                <p>Ankara may wish consider desirability <persName corresp="#p_HLW1"
                        >Henderson</persName>’s conveying this information to King.</p>
                <p>Amman should inform Rifai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
